<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-06T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-06T18:00:00-05:00" n="462" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d462">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/12–144: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-06T19:00:00-04:00">December 6, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>712. Dept concurs in position taken in your conversation with the
                                Prime Minister, as reported in urtel 890, December 1. Dept believes
                                that, in view of intervening developments you acted wisely in
                                refraining from informing Iranian authorities of the purport of our
                                679, November 20.<note n="45" xml:id="d462fn45">See footnote 43,
                                        <ref target="#pg_436">p. 436</ref>.</note> The intent of
                                that message was not to suggest Gresham as a possible successor to
                                Millspaugh but merely to express concurrence in his continued
                                service in Iran as an American who has demonstrated good performance
                                and cooperation with the Iranians.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>